9e9-a555-4105-a53e-2bf88534eb28" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">site</xref>, Ultimate Limit State (ULS) wind pressure set out in AS 4055, and the dimensions of the glass panel. AS 4055 has higher ULS wind pressures for parts of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_b7de8ae6-abb6-4268-93bc-1d5fc2be3ffa" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">external walls</xref> within 1200 mm of external corners. The thickness of glass in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4818_0.11.0.xml#_6624e74a-cd3e-4a72-b89c-56870e19af0e" id="_d59b3a40-12ca-4db5-b102-6cf4d07528c4" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Tables 8.3.3a</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4819_0.9.0.xml#_b327e425-8060-4cac-b224-a20a19adb7f0" id="_299bfcf4-a783-4dcd-b7f6-03b9e3d641ae" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">8.3.3b</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4820_0.9.0.xml#_2e7627c6-2ee3-49e3-ae9e-c0f593831ed2" id="_cb8808a9-ec8d-47b2-aea4-74e73d7f232a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">8.3.3c</xref> is based on these higher ULS wind pressures and can also be used for glass in the general length of walls.</li></ul></callout></clause>